  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Inflammatory reaction in different compartments of the body may have a negative effect on
      outcome. This study assesses the inflammatory reaction systemically, intrapulmonary and
      intrapleural by measuring different cytokines. Patients with lung cancer undergoing lobectomy
      or segmentectomy are included in the study. Hypothesis: The inflammatory reaction in the
      pleural space is high compared to the systemic and intrapulmonary ones.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
